@page "/Privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - TagzApp</PageTitle>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p><em>Last updated: @(new DateTime(2025,9,2).ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy"))</em></p>

    <h2>Our Commitment to Privacy</h2>
    <p>
        TagzApp is committed to protecting your privacy. We believe in transparency about how we collect, use, and share information about you. 
        This privacy policy explains our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of information that we receive through our service.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    
    <h3>Public Social Media Content</h3>
    <p>
        TagzApp aggregates and displays content from public social media networks and platforms. All content displayed in TagzApp is:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Already publicly available on the respective social media platforms</li>
        <li>Accessible without requiring user authentication or private access</li>
        <li>Subject to the privacy policies and terms of service of the originating social media platforms</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Technical Information</h3>
    <p>
        When you use TagzApp, we may automatically collect certain technical information, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Your IP address and general location information</li>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Device information and operating system</li>
        <li>Pages visited and time spent on our service</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What We Don't Collect</h2>
    <p>TagzApp does not:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Require user registration or account creation</li>
        <li>Collect personal information such as names, email addresses, or phone numbers for regular users.  Only moderators and administrators need to share this information.</li>
        <li>Access private or protected social media content</li>
        <li>Store user credentials or login information for social media accounts</li>
        <li>Track users across other websites or services</li>
        <li>Collect sensitive personal information</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>The information we collect is used solely to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide and maintain our service</li>
        <li>Improve user experience and service functionality</li>
        <li>Monitor and analyze usage patterns to enhance our service</li>
        <li>Ensure the security and proper functioning of our platform</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>
        We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your information to third parties, except in the following circumstances:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>When required by law or legal process</li>
        <li>To protect our rights, property, or safety, or that of our users or the public</li>
        <li>In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets (with prior notice)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational security measures to protect the information we process. However, 
        no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
        TagzApp displays content from various social media platforms. Each platform has its own privacy policy and terms of service:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Content displayed from these platforms is governed by their respective privacy policies</li>
        <li>We encourage you to review the privacy policies of these third-party services</li>
        <li>We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external platforms</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
        We retain technical information only as long as necessary to provide our service and for legitimate business purposes. 
        Public social media content is cached temporarily to improve performance but is not permanently stored beyond operational needs.
    </p>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Know what information we collect about you</li>
        <li>Request deletion of any information we may have collected</li>
        <li>Opt-out of any data collection by discontinuing use of our service</li>
        <li>Contact us with privacy-related questions or concerns</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>
        TagzApp does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 years of age. If we become aware that we have 
        inadvertently collected such information, we will take steps to delete it promptly.
    </p>

    <h2>International Users</h2>
    <p>
        TagzApp may be accessed from countries around the world. By using our service, you consent to the collection and processing 
        of information in accordance with this privacy policy, regardless of your location.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time. When we do, we will post the updated policy on this page and update 
        the "Last updated" date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your information.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
        If you have any questions about this privacy policy or our privacy practices, please contact us through at
        <a href="mailto:contact@@tagzapp.net">our contact email address</a>.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-4" />
    
    <p class="text-muted">
        <small>
            This privacy policy is designed to be transparent about our minimal data collection practices. 
            TagzApp is committed to protecting your privacy while providing a useful service for viewing public social media content.
        </small>
    </p>
</div>
